why does writing things down reinforce the memory so much when i write things down those things get done even if i never look at it again if i rely solely on my memory to do things things get cluttered forgotton and put off why does writing things down help so much even if i write it down and throw away the paper seeing your thoughts plans verbalized on paper locks them in as floating thoughts are like little bubbles of abstractions once you've written it doesn't matter if you throw it away the cement is there served its purpose writing as in a journal is also an excellent way to clarify your sometimes chaotic or unresolved feelings of course i don't mean i went to the po today so so called stuff for me it's a little bell ringing that draws me to the pc at what seem the most unlikely moments but always as i follow my stream of consciousness insights associations simply appear almost like automatic writing i've written my to do list yet not even rferring to it at the end of the day hopefully i'll have accomplished everything on it writing is very important to me in many different ways it has another dimension i'd always prefer a letter to a phone call something i can look at again again not words spoken that blow away in the wind sadly this seems an almost totally lost art i'd also rather read a book than watch a movie i'm mentioning my way only to indicate what i believe is the importance of writing it reinforces clarifies Philosophy of language Deconstruction CPU cache Objective-C Religious Society of Friends Rhetoric Milton H. Erickson The Amber Spyglass Second language acquisition Consciousness Maurice Merleau-Ponty Marshall McLuhan David Hume Yoga Sutras of Patanjali Memento (film) Dyslexia Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind Theory of conduct Sigmund Freud Annuity Behaviorism The Pilgrim's Progress The SpongeBob SquarePants Movie Ludwig Wittgenstein Traumatic incident reduction Mathematics About a Boy Time Out of Mind Jiddu Krishnamurti Modem The Book of Five